; PaideiaOS IPC Phase-1 Benchmark: SPSC Throughput
; P3-017: Microbenchmark for single-producer single-consumer channel throughput
; Design reference: design/ipc/phase1-api.md §6

module IpcSpscPerf

; Benchmark: Measure enqueue/dequeue throughput under steady-state conditions

; Constants
BENCH_CHANNEL_CAPACITY = 16      ; Small capacity to maintain steady-state flow
BENCH_SLOT_SIZE = 256
BENCH_ITERATION_COUNT = 10000    ; Number of enqueue/dequeue pairs
BENCH_MESSAGE_SIZE = 32          ; Typical message size

; Workload:
; 1. ipc_create_channel(16, 256)
; 2. Start timer
; 3. Loop 10000 times:
;    a. ipc_enqueue(producer_cap, message, 32)
;    b. ipc_dequeue(consumer_cap, output_buffer, 256)
; 4. End timer
; 5. Report throughput: iterations per second, cycles per operation

; Expected result (Phase 7+ baseline):
; On a 3.0 GHz CPU, expect ~1-2 cycles per enqueue + ~1-2 cycles per dequeue
; for cache-hot operation, yielding ~1 billion ops/sec.
; This is a baseline for evaluating phase-2 optimizations (wait-free, etc).

; STUB: Constants and benchmark outline only
; Runtime: Deferred to paideia-as Phase 7+

end module
